{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This architecture effectively improves the accuracy of 3D human pose estimation through multi-scale and multi-level feature learning methods, combined with new skeletal pool and skeletal unpool operations.",
    "To estimate 3D human and 3D hand poses from short sequences of 2D joint detections, (Cai et al. 2019) proposed a graph pooling layer and an upsampling layer designed using graph convolutional network and graph pooling techniques in combination with interpretable human body (or hand) configurations, which efficiently integrates information of different resolutions and improves the accuracy of 3D pose estimation.",
    "Finally, (Han et al. 2022) proposed vision graph neural networks (ViG) to revolutionize the image-to-graph structure transformation method, which effectively reduces the spatial scale of graphs through graph pooling techniques and provides high-quality graph-level feature representations for subsequent vision tasks.",
    "These works demonstrate the central role of graph pooling techniques in advancing the field of computer vision.",
    "In urban computing application fields, graph pooling techniques have demonstrated their unique value and application potential, especially in critical tasks such as urban area representation learning, Urban Knowledge Graph (UrbanKG) construction, urban spatiotemporal mobility prediction, urban traffic flow analysis, and Short-term Quantitative Precipitation Forecasting (SQPF)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To estimate 3D human and 3D hand poses from short sequences of 2D joint detections, (Cai et al. 2019) proposed a graph pooling layer and an upsampling layer designed using graph convolutional network and graph pooling techniques in combination with interpretable human body (or hand) configurations, which efficiently integrates information of different resolutions and improves the accuracy of 3D pose estimation.",
    "Finally, (Han et al. 2022) proposed vision graph neural networks (ViG) to revolutionize the image-to-graph structure transformation method, which effectively reduces the spatial scale of graphs through graph pooling techniques and provides high-quality graph-level feature representations for subsequent vision tasks."
